    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Getting the coordiantes of our DEM:\n",
        "`dem.boudns` gives us the latitude and longitude that we can further use"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T16Z59fDDhBN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import rasterio\n",
        "dem = rasterio.open('/content/drive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/solar_radiation/bazmandem.tif')\n",
        "#left edge\n",
        "long_left = dem.bounds[0]\n",
        "print(long_left)\n",
        "#bottom edge\n",
        "lat_butt = dem.bounds[1]\n",
        "print(lat_butt)\n",
        "#right edge\n",
        "long_right = dem.bounds[2]\n",
        "print(long_right)\n",
        "#top edge\n",
        "lat_top = dem.bounds[3]\n",
        "print(lat_top)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Latitude and longitude of each pixel\n",
        "creating two rasters, one contaiong latitude of each pixel and one for longitude\n",
        "we are interpolating each pixel lat and long using linespace\n",
        "\n",
        "there are so many things going on in this function so I'll try to explain them all:\n",
        "\n",
        "`np.linspace(start,stop,numer)`: so our latitude is the same for each row, what we do here is that with linspace we care only one column of the lat raster,\n",
        "which is from `top_lat` to `buttom_lat` and with the step number of number of rows in original dem(in this case 3601)\n",
        "\n",
        "`[:,None]` what this does it converst a row wise array into a column wise array\n",
        "\n",
        "[np.tile()](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/21482728/how-to-fill-a-numpy-array-with-a-gradient-with-a-vectorized-code): what this does is it takse a row or column an it repreats it in rows or columns, with this now we can multiply our 1 column lat into width columns lat_raster\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fOm9Ypz7IW8O"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "```python\n",
        "In [422]: np.tile((0,1,2), (5,1))\n",
        "Out[422]: \n",
        "array([[0, 1, 2],\n",
        "       [0, 1, 2],\n",
        "       [0, 1, 2],\n",
        "       [0, 1, 2],\n",
        "       [0, 1, 2]])\n",
        "\n",
        "In [473]: tile(arange(5)[:,None], 3)\n",
        "Out[473]: \n",
        "array([[0, 0, 0],\n",
        "       [1, 1, 1],\n",
        "       [2, 2, 2],\n",
        "       [3, 3, 3],\n",
        "       [4, 4, 4]])\n",
        "```"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Wpu82GS_Eqk5"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def lat_raster_creator(dem, top_lat,butt_lat):\n",
        "  height,width = dem.shape\n",
        "  column = np.linspace(top_lat,butt_lat,height)[:,None]\n",
        "  lat_ras = np.tile(column,width)\n",
        "  return lat_ras\n",
        "\n",
        "def long_raster_creator(dem, long_left,long_right):\n",
        "  height,width = dem.shape\n",
        "  row = np.linspace(long_left,long_right,width)\n",
        "  lat_ras = np.tile(row,(height,1))\n",
        "  return lat_ras"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3wemxxRyEJ7H"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

      "source": [
        "## sun position function\n",
        "this func takes lat,long and time, and will return sun `altitude angle`, `zenith angle`, and `azimuth angle` in **degrees**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6fZ0Nkf39c6p"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def sun_position(lat_long,date,time_hr,country_time_zone_utc=4.5):\n",
        "  '''\n",
        "  lat_long is a tupple like (28.3,60.1)\n",
        "  date is a tupple like (year,month,day)\n",
        "  time_hr is time of the day in 24hr format\n",
        "  '''\n",
        "  y = date[0]\n",
        "  m = date[1]\n",
        "  d = date[2]\n",
        "  dobj = datetime.datetime(y,m,d,time_hr,tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc) - datetime.timedelta(hours=country_time_zone_utc)\n",
        "\n",
        "  #lat long\n",
        "  alt =  ps.get_altitude(lat_long[0],lat_long[1], dobj) # sun altitude angle\n",
        "  sza = float(90) - alt #sun zenith angle\n",
        "  azm = ps.get_azimuth(lat_long[0],lat_long[1], dobj) #sun azimuth angle\n",
        "  return {'alt':alt,'zen':sza,'azm':azm}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "B9cwfu6RGQLi"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",

      "cell_type": "code",

        "from ipywidgets import IntProgress\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Sun's position raster\n",
        "now that we have a function to calculate sun's positions we can apply it for each pixel of a raster - of course it will take a lot of time but leads to a greate percision"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "39y1wv3-B2U_"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#THIS FUNCTION IS OUTDATED AND WILL BE OVERWIRTED IN THE NEXT CELL WHERE WE ADD DOWN_SAMPLING FACTOR\n",
        "\n",
        "def sun_poistion_raster_creator(lat_raster,long_raster,date,time_hr,country_time_zone_utc=4.5):\n",
        "  # f is for the progress bar\n",
        "  f = IntProgress(min=0, max=lat_raster.shape[0]*lat_raster.shape[1]) # instantiate the bar\n",
        "  display(f) # display the bar\n",
        "\n",
        "  \n",
        "  alt_ras = np.zeros(lat_raster.shape) # creating empty arrays the same size as original dem to be filled later\n",
        "  zen_ras = np.zeros(lat_raster.shape)\n",
        "  azm_ras = np.zeros(lat_raster.shape)\n",
        "\n",
        "  counter  = 0 #just for printing the process progress\n",
        "  for y, x in np.ndindex(lat_raster.shape): # you can use longitude_raster as well there is no diffrence\n",
        "    #ndindex returns index of each row and column it is currently at\n",
        "    f.value += 1\n",
        "\n",
        "    lat = lat_raster[y,x]\n",
        "    lng = long_raster[y,x]\n",
        "    sp = sun_position((lat,lng) , date , time_hr,country_time_zone_utc) #calculating angle for each pixel\n",
        "    alt_ras[y,x] = sp['alt']\n",
        "    zen_ras[y,x] = sp['zen']\n",
        "    azm_ras[y,x] = sp['azm']\n",
        "  \n",
        "  return {'alt_ras':alt_ras,'zen_ras':zen_ras,'azm_ras':azm_ras}"
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Sun's position raster but with downsampling factor:\n",
        "so as we saw in the previous function it takse a lot of time calculation solar postion, so in this new function we are introducting the `down_sample_factor`\n",
        "when it is equal to `1 (or less than 1)` everything is like before, but when we change it to somthing more that `1` for example `2` we resize the image into half of its dimentstions, then we do the calculations, and after that we upsample the image into its original size, like this we loose percision but we can achive a lot faster reasults.\n",
        "\n",
        "NOTE:  be aware that there is a stupoid thing about `cv2` and that is `cv2.resize()` takes (col,row) insted of (row,col) so thats why we reversed the tuple."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "u4sno6b8NUqB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def sun_poistion_raster_creator(lat_raster,long_raster,date,time_hr,country_time_zone_utc=4.5,down_sample_factor=1):\n",
        "  '''\n",
        "  when down_sample_factor is equal to `1 (or less than 1)` everything is like before,\n",
        "  but when we change it to somthing more that `1` for example `2` we resize the image\n",
        "  into half of its dimentstions, then we do the calculations, and after that we upsample\n",
        "  the image into its original size, like this we loose percision but we can achive a lot faster reasults.\n",
        "  '''\n",
        "\n",
        "  org_shape = lat_raster.shape\n",
        "  rows,cols = lat_raster.shape\n",
        "  org_shape= org_shape[::-1]\n",
        "  \n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "  if down_sample_factor > 1:\n",
        "    rows = int(rows/down_sample_factor)\n",
        "    cols = int(cols/down_sample_factor)\n",
        "    lat_raster = cv.resize(lat_raster,(cols,rows),cv.INTER_LINEAR)\n",
        "    long_raster = cv.resize(long_raster,(cols,rows),cv.INTER_LINEAR)\n",
        "\n",
        "  # f is for the progress bar\n",
        "  f = IntProgress(min=0, max=rows*cols) # instantiate the bar\n",
        "  display(f) # display the bar\n",
        "  \n",
        "  alt_ras = np.zeros((rows,cols)) # creating empty arrays the same size as original dem to be filled later\n",
        "  zen_ras = np.zeros((rows,cols))\n",
        "  azm_ras = np.zeros((rows,cols))\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "  counter  = 0 #just for printing the process progress\n",
        "  for y, x in np.ndindex(lat_raster.shape): # you can use longitude_raster as well there is no diffrence\n",
        "    #ndindex returns index of each row and column it is currently at\n",
        "    f.value += 1\n",
        "  \n",
        "\n",
        "    lat = lat_raster[y,x]\n",
        "    lng = long_raster[y,x]\n",
        "    sp = sun_position((lat,lng) , date , time_hr,country_time_zone_utc) #calculating angle for each pixel\n",
        "    alt_ras[y,x] = sp['alt']\n",
        "    zen_ras[y,x] = sp['zen']\n",
        "    azm_ras[y,x] = sp['azm']\n",
        "\n",
        "  if down_sample_factor > 1:\n",
        "    alt_ras = cv.resize(alt_ras,org_shape,cv.INTER_LINEAR)\n",
        "    zen_ras = cv.resize(zen_ras,org_shape,cv.INTER_LINEAR)\n",
        "    azm_ras = cv.resize(azm_ras,org_shape,cv.INTER_LINEAR)\n",
        "  \n",
        "  return {'alt_ras':alt_ras,'zen_ras':zen_ras,'azm_ras':azm_ras}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ChtiOLZqFkNw"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

        "from numpy import cos,sin,radians"

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Solar incident angle:\n",
        "\n",
        "this how we we find the exact incident angle for each pixel:\n",
        "\n",
        "`cos_i = cos(s) * cos(z) + sin(s) * sin(z) * cos(a - o)`\n",
        "\n",
        "<img src='https://grass.osgeo.org/grass78/manuals/i_topo_corr_angles.png'>\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HaIUIiHcTXAT"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def solar_incident_angle(slope_raster,solar_zenith_raster,solar_azimuth_raster,aspect_raster):\n",
        "  s= radians(slope_raster)\n",
        "  z= radians(solar_zenith_raster)\n",
        "  a= radians(solar_azimuth_raster)\n",
        "  o= radians(aspect_raster)\n",
        "\n",
        "  cos_i = cos(s) * cos(z) + sin(s) * sin(z) * cos(a - o)\n",
        "\n",
        "  return np.degrees(np.arccos(cos_i))\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZZi2XsgGZ4_k"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "sun_incident_ras = solar_incident_angle(slp,sun_pos_ras['zen_ras'],sun_pos_ras['azm_ras'],asp)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nPC-Zl5tbN4n"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Coolbaugh formula directly from Dr.Kiavarz notes"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "I8oiBF2le8Tm"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "![image.png](data:image/png;base64,)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ikFuPirSe0eW"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def coolbaugh(solar_zenith_raster,solar_incident_raster):\n",
        "  z =radians(solar_zenith_raster)\n",
        "  s0 = 1367 #[w*m^2]\n",
        "  mz = 1 - (0.2/(cos(z)**2))\n",
        "  zp  = radians(solar_incident_raster)\n",
        "\n",
        "  cb  = s0 * mz * cos(zp)\n",
        "\n",
        "  return cb"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HCuAK6gHb3-Z"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "ise = coolbaugh(sun_pos_ras['zen_ras'],sun_incident_ras) # ise = inicident solar energy"
      ],

        "id": "Np8Qh3RId13q"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Coolbaugh through out the day"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "LVV-A5Nlp-2T"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def coobaugh_day(slope_raster,aspect_raster,lat_raster,long_raster,date,time_hour_start=6,time_hour_end=17,country_time_zone_utc=4.5 ,down_sample_factor=1):\n",
        "  sun_pos_ras_list = []\n",
        "  for t in np.arange(time_hour_start,time_hour_end+1):\n",
        "    sun_pos_ras_list.append(sun_poistion_raster_creator(lat_raster,long_raster, date , t,country_time_zone_utc,down_sample_factor))\n",
        "\n",
        "  sun_incident_ras_list = []\n",
        "  for sun_pos_ras in sun_pos_ras_list:\n",
        "    sun_incident_ras_list.append(solar_incident_angle(slope_raster,sun_pos_ras['zen_ras'],sun_pos_ras['azm_ras'],aspect_raster))\n",
        "\n",
        "  ise_list = []\n",
        "  for sun_pos_ras,sun_incident_ras in zip(sun_pos_ras_list,sun_incident_ras_list):\n",
        "    ise_list.append(coolbaugh(sun_pos_ras['zen_ras'],sun_incident_ras))\n",
        "  \n",
        "  #delay factor list should be like [1/2n , ... , 1/4 , 1/2 , 1]\n",
        "  #the closest the hour the more effect it has\n",
        "  df_list = []\n",
        "  for d in range(len(ise_list)):\n",
        "    df_list.append(1/2**d)\n",
        "  df_list.reverse()\n",
        "\n",
        "  cb_sum = 0\n",
        "  for e,d in zip(ise_list,df_list):\n",
        "    cb_sum += e*d\n",
        "  \n",
        "  return {'cb_sum':cb_sum , 'ise_list':ise_list ,'df_list':df_list,'sun_incident_ras_list':sun_incident_ras_list,'sun_pos_ras_list':sun_pos_ras_list}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GEjZmnFZeat-"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
